<TITLE> Truck crash kills 5 homebound in Kurigram </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Kurigram, Dec 7 (bdnews24.com)Five people were killed and 17 injured, on their way back to family homes for Eid, as a truck overturned in Kurigram early Sunday, police said. Roumari police chief Akbar Ali told bdnews24.com that the passengers taking a low-cost ride back home on a cargo carrier on the eve of Eid-ul-Azha met with the tragic accident at Batargram village in Dantbhanga, Roumari. The accident victims were identified as Shamer Ali, 22, and Jahangir Alam, 20, from Char Italukanda and Kofiluddin, 18, Hamed, 20, and Rashid Molla, 21, from Shantir Char, Ali said. The dead bodies have been handed over to family members. The injured, also from Char Italukanda and Shantir Char villages, were admitted to Roumari upazila health complex and Kurigram Sadar Hospital for treatment. Two were sent on to Rangpur Medical College Hospital, said the police chief. "The truck coming from Tangail overturned as its driver tried to avoid a roadside breach," he told bdnews24.com. Dantbhanga UP chairman Fazlul Haque said, "About 70 labourers from Char Italukanda and Shantir Char villages had gone out to Hatubhanga in Tangail to work at a brickfield." "They had hired the truck on the eve of the Eid-ul-Azha to return home." The truck driver and his assistant fled the scene, police said. A case has been filed with Roumari police. Roumari upazila nirbahi officer Md Hanifuddin said local administrativon was taking steps to assist the families of the deceased. bdne
